CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1960, pg. 5 reads: "7. Alma Johns, consultant for Personal Products Corp., Milltown, N.J., makers of Modess, and teen-ager Carey Jasper, Gladstone Junior High, Pittsburgh, passed out literature vital to all women visitors."
TitMainTitle: Alma Johns and Carey Jasper, seated in Personal Products Corporation booth in Syria Mosque for the 1960 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama
